<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Cluster2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Cluster,</orth> vb., to grow in bunches: <cit><quote>--ing filberts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.175" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 175</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>vines with --ing bunches,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.112.175" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 112</bibl></cit>. Used of a throng: <cit><quote>to start into the --ing battle of the French,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.7.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 7, 13</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>